rComments: He refused to speak with me on a number of occasions & I had a difficult time communicating with him by e-mail. The course was attendance based & I missed more than the allotted amount for medical reasons (proven with doctor's note) but he refused to look at it. He failed me. I dropped French Immersion the following semester, feeling angry & hurt.

Very smart man but cannot teach at all.  He does not respond to emails, will not meet with you and will not give any structured guidelines for projects or tests.  I got a D+ in his course and I've taken 12 FLS courses at this university and never got less than a B.
